> Source attribution conflicts on this drink: Joe Scialom is widely cited as the Hawaii Kai's beverage director after his Shepheard's/Cairo years, while Mannie Andal was head bartender and is credited by some sources with the specific creation.[^1][^2] Garnish traditionally included a "pearl" (a pearl onion or sugar pearl) alongside the gardenia.[^3] The lime is dialed back to 0.75 oz here — the Hawaiian Kai 1970 Cookbook source called for 2 oz, which yields an undrinkable acid bomb and is likely a transcription anomaly.[^3]
>
> Brand recommendations. Best: Don Q Añejo or Bacardi Reserva Ocho for the Puerto Rican rum; Pierre Ferrand Dry Curaçao for the orange curaçao; B.G. Reynolds or Small Hand Foods orgeat; raw orange-blossom honey for the honey syrup; fresh half-and-half. Economical: Bacardi Gold or Don Q Gold for the Puerto Rican rum; Senior Curaçao of Curaçao or Bols Orange Curaçao; Liber & Co. orgeat or Fee Brothers; supermarket clover honey; supermarket half-and-half.

In a #blender{} combine @fresh lime juice{0.75%oz}, @fresh grapefruit juice{1%oz}, @honey syrup{0.5%oz} (1:1), @orgeat syrup{0.5%oz}, @half-and-half{0.5%oz}, @orange curaçao{0.5%oz}, and @Puerto Rican rum{1.5%oz}.

Add @crushed ice{0.5%cup} and blend on high for about 10 seconds.

Pour unstrained into a #tiki mug{} or large goblet.

Garnish with a @gardenia{1} and a @pearl{1}.

> A sugar pearl or pearl onion is traditional for the pearl garnish.

> [^1]: Berry, *Beachbum Berry Remixed* (2010), Hawaii Kai entries — discusses the New York Hawaii Kai room (Broadway and 50th, c. 1962), Joe Scialom's beverage-director role after his Cairo / Shepheard's years, and Mannie Andal's parallel head-bartender credit.
> [^2]: Mustipher, *Tiki: Modern Tropical Cocktails* (2019), Joe Scialom / Hawaii Kai entries — documents Scialom's transitional role from Cairo refugee bartender to American tiki-room beverage director.
> [^3]: Kindred Cocktails, "Hawaii Kai Treasure." https://kindredcocktails.com/cocktail/hawaii-kai-treasure (accessed 2026-05-03) — frontmatter source URL; reproduces the Hawaiian Kai 1970 Cookbook spec (with the 2 oz lime that is treated here as a transcription anomaly) and the gardenia-and-pearl garnish.
